#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""One-file builder for the FRED Credit-Risk Dashboard (KeyBank style).

Why this exists: emailing the .xlsx binary kept getting rewritten/blocked by
corporate security. This script is plain ASCII (the code is base64 inside), so
it survives email/DLP intact. Run it on the target machine and it BUILDS the
workbook locally -- nothing binary to corrupt.

USAGE (PowerShell):
    python -m pip install pandas openpyxl      # fredapi too, for live data
    python build_dashboard.py

It writes into the current folder:
    runner.py, macro.bas, requirements.txt, and
    FRED_Credit_Risk_Dashboard.xlsx  (demo-populated, opens showing the dashboards)

Then: open the .xlsx. For live FRED data, set FRED_API_KEY and run:
    python runner.py --workbook ".\\FRED_Credit_Risk_Dashboard.xlsx" --backend openpyxl
"""
